==A Missing Fox==
===Talking to Guildmaster Apatura===
* {{tcond|If the player does not meet the quest's requirements:}}
** '''Guildmaster Apatura:''' Sorry, but you need to be a better hunter before we can help you out.
** {{tbox|You need 46 Hunter to access Hunter Guild amenities.}}
** {{tact|end}}
* '''Guildmaster Apatura:''' Oh, you're a new face around here, aren't you?
* '''Player:''' I am indeed. Just exploring the savannah.
* '''Guildmaster Apatura:''' Well, I'm Apatura. Let me welcome you to our small corner of Varlamore.
* {{tselect|Select an Option}}
* {{topt|What do you do here?}}
** '''Player:''' What do you do here?
** '''Guildmaster Apatura:''' We're mostly here to keep an eye on the local animal populations, and provide animal parts to the city.
** '''Guildmaster Apatura:''' As for me personally, I'm the current master of this guild.
** '''Player:''' Current master?
** '''Guildmaster Apatura:''' A hunter's work is dangerous. We tend to go through members faster than other guilds. That said, I'm usually too busy with politics and paperwork to go out hunting these days.
** '''Player:''' Could I hunt with the guild?
** '''Guildmaster Apatura:''' Absolutely! There's always more work to be done. Head down into the Burrow and talk to the other hunters to get an idea of what we need help with.
* {{topt|Can I help you with anything?}}
** '''Player:''' Can I help you with anything?
** '''Guildmaster Apatura:''' I'm not sure if you have the time or the patience, iknami, but a little birdy told me that our esteemed scribe Verity may require some assistance.
** '''Player:''' What sort of assistance?
** '''Guildmaster Apatura:''' If I had to guess, she needs someone to find something for her.
** '''Guildmaster Apatura:''' She's a wonderful scribe, but can lose some strange things here and there.
** {{tselect|Start the At First Light quest?}}
** {{topt|Yes.}}
*** '''Player:''' Great! Point me in her direction and I'll get cracking!
*** '''Guildmaster Apatura:''' She's behind the bar in the Burrow. Just look for the stressed woman trying to wrangle a bunch of barely- bathed hunters.
*** {{tact|end}}
** {{topt|No.}}
*** '''Player:''' I'm not sure I have the time for that right now.
*** '''Guildmaster Apatura:''' Tetamo... Well, hopefully it's not too important.
*** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|I'd better be off.}}
** '''Player:''' I'd better be off.
** {{tact|end}}

====Talking to Apatura again====
* '''Guildmaster Apatura:''' Nilsal, hunter.
* '''Player:''' Nilsal, Apatura.
* {{tselect|Select an Option}}
* {{topt|What do you do here?}}
** {{tact|above}}
* {{topt|Are you free to talk about my quest?}}
** '''Player:''' Are you free to talk about my quest?
** '''Guildmaster Apatura:''' Absolutely. Have you spoken to Verity yet?
** '''Player:''' No, not quite yet.
** '''Guildmaster Apatura:''' If you're having a hard time finding her, she's behind the bar in the Burrow. Head down the stairs in the big tree. You can't miss it, and if you can, maybe you're not cut out for the Hunter Guild.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|I'd better be off.}}
** {{tact|above}}

===Talking to Guild Scribe Verity===
* {{tcond|If the player has never talked to Guild Scribe Verity:}}
** '''Guild Scribe Verity:''' Oh, hello there newcomer. I'm Guild Scribe Verity. Do you need me to explain the work we do here?
** '''Player:''' Yes please.
** '''Guild Scribe Verity:''' So it's nice and simple. Just chat to any of the hunters in here to help them out. They're all following reports that I've split up amongst them.
** '''Player:''' Reports?
** '''Guild Scribe Verity:''' Indeed. There are all sorts of interesting creatures to hunt out there. Sometimes we get reports of a particularly unique example. When that happens, one of the hunters will set out to find it.
** '''Guild Scribe Verity:''' If you do decide to take a job from any of the hunters, they'll tell you what type of creature they're looking into. Hunt that creature until you encounter the unique specimen.
** '''Guild Scribe Verity:''' Once you've caught it, bring some proof back to the hunter that sent you out in the first place. I'm sure they'll reward you for your time.
** '''Player:''' I see. Thanks for the information.
** '''Guild Scribe Verity:''' Now, what else can I do for you.
** '''Player:''' Well actually, I heard there might be something I could help you with?
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{tcond|If the player has previously talked to Guild Scribe Verity:}}
** '''Player:''' Hi Verity. I heard there might be something I could help you with?
** {{tact|continues}}
* '''Guild Scribe Verity:''' You'll have to be slightly more specific. There's always something that needs doing down here!
* '''Player:''' Something a little birdy may have told Apatura?
* '''Guild Scribe Verity:''' Tetamo... Pitri needs to stop twittering with the birds. Yes, Gilman and I are concerned about Fox. He left quietly in the night, but we have no record of what he was doing.
* '''Player:''' Do you normally keep track of the hunters here?
* '''Guild Scribe Verity:''' We try to, but it's like herding cats! We at least like to keep an eye on what they're hunting and point them in the right direction. It prevents us from losing track of too many creatures... or people.
* '''Player:''' Could anyone else have put Fox onto a hunt?
* '''Guild Scribe Verity:''' If anyone did, it would've been Wolf. She's always getting Fox into some kind of trouble.
* '''Player:''' I'll follow up with her then.
* {{tact|end}}

====Talking to Verity again====
* '''Guild Scribe Verity:''' Have you spoken to Wolf yet?
* '''Player:''' Not yet. I'll have a chat to her now.
* {{tact|end}}

===Talking to Guildmaster Apatura after talking to Verity===
* '''Guildmaster Apatura:''' Nilsal, hunter.
* '''Player:''' Nilsal, Apatura.
* {{tselect|Select an Option}}
* {{topt|quest=No|What do you do here?}}
* {{topt|Are you free to talk about my quest?}}
** '''Player:''' Are you free to talk about my quest?
** '''Guildmaster Apatura:''' Absolutely. So was our little birdy right about Verity needing a hand?
** '''Player:''' They were... It wasn't an actual bird was it?
** '''Guildmaster Apatura:''' Of course not. Only Pitri talks to the birds.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|quest=No|I'd better be off.}}

===Talking to Guild Hunter Wolf===
* '''Guild Hunter Wolf (Master):''' So, here to ask me what trouble I've gotten Fox into, are you?
* '''Player:''' That's not quite how I'd word it... but how did you know?
* '''Guild Hunter Wolf (Master):''' I've honed my instincts over the years.
* '''Guild Hunter Wolf (Master):''' Well, that and the fact you had that whole conversation within earshot.
* '''Player:''' Right... So did you send Fox out to do something?
* '''Guild Hunter Wolf (Master):''' Sort of. He's on some very unofficial business for me.
* '''Player:''' How unofficial?
* '''Guild Hunter Wolf (Master):''' If I told you... I'd have to kill you!
* '''Player:''' ...
* '''Guild Hunter Wolf (Master):''' Your face! Don't worry, I'm just pulling your leg.
* '''Guild Hunter Wolf (Master):''' I asked him to look into making some repairs to Kiko's bed. It's been getting tatty lately. I'm guessing he didn't end up having the materials needed. That'll be why he headed out.
* '''Player:''' Well then I guess the first step is to work out what he went to get. Could I take a look at Kiko's bed?
* '''Guild Hunter Wolf (Master):''' You're welcome to try, but you'll need to convince Kiko to let you. He's just by the table there.
* '''Player:''' Any advice for convincing him?
* '''Guild Hunter Wolf (Master):''' He's very easy to distract. We have a little fake mouse we use sometimes.
* {{tcond|If the player has no inventory space:}}
** '''Player:''' Could I borrow it when I have a free hand to take it?
** '''Guild Hunter Wolf (Master):''' Sure thing.
** {{tact|end}}
* '''Player:''' Could I borrow it to have a go at distracting him?
* '''Guild Hunter Wolf (Master):''' Absolutely!
* {{tbox|pic=Toy mouse detail.png|Wolf hands you a small toy mouse.}}
* {{tact|end}}

====Talking to Wolf again====
* '''Guild Hunter Wolf (Master):''' Have you checked Kiko's bed yet? It's just to the side of this table.
* {{tcond|If the player has inventory space and has not yet gotten the mouse:}}
** '''Player:''' Not yet. Could I grab that mouse to distract him with?
** '''Guild Hunter Wolf (Master):''' Absolutely.
** {{tbox|pic=Toy mouse detail.png|Wolf hands you a small toy mouse.}}
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tcond|If the player has the toy mouse in their inventory:}}
** '''Player:''' Not yet. I'll get to it now.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tcond|If the player lost the toy mouse:}}
** '''Player:''' Not yet. Do you happen to have that mouse to distract him with?
** '''Guild Hunter Wolf (Master):''' I already gave it to you. If you've lost it, you'll need to get another for yourself. I'd do so quickly if I were you. Kiko won't be happy if he finds out it's gone.
** {{tact|end}}

===Petting Kiko===
* {{tcond|If the player doesn't have a catspeak amulet or Dragon Slayer II completed:}}
** {{mes|You pet the cat, who leans into your hand in return.}}
* '''Guild Hunter Kiko:''' Can you scratch my belly next? It's perfectly safe.
* {{tact|end}}

===Using an unwound toy mouse on Kiko===
* '''Guild Hunter Kiko:''' Are you not going to wind it up first? Come on now, put some effort in.
* {{tact|end}}

===Checking the cat bed===
* '''Guild Hunter Kiko:''' Do you mind? I'm trying to sleep here.
* {{tcond|If the player has a toy mouse (wound):}}
** '''Player:''' Here you go, little guy.
** '''Guild Hunter Kiko:''' A mouse? Fantastic!
** {{tbox|You check the cat's bed. It sure could use a little bit of love... and a lot of repairs. It's made of a luxurious fluffy fur that you don't recognise. It looks like someone has intentionally cut off a small bit of it.}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Using a wound toy mouse on Kiko or the cat bed===
* '''Player:''' Here you go, little guy.
* {{tbox|pic=Toy mouse detail.png|Kiko happily starts playing with the toy mouse.}}
* {{tact|above}}

====Checking the bed again====
* {{tbox|You see that the cat's bed is unsurprisingly still in need of repairs.}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Talking to Wolf after inspecting the cat bed===
* '''Player:''' I managed to have a look at that bed. I've never seen such luxury material for a cat bed before.
* '''Guild Hunter Wolf (Master):''' Only the best for our Kiko.
* '''Player:''' I'm guessing it's the actual fur itself that Fox will be looking to replace. It looks like he cut a small bit off. I don't suppose you know where he'd have gone to get that.
* '''Guild Hunter Wolf (Master):''' We have a contact who lives in Outer Fortis. She stocks the best of the best when it comes to fabrics. That'll be where he went, but knowing Fox, he won't have gone directly there.
* '''Player:''' Why not?
* '''Guild Hunter Wolf (Master):''' He'll have stopped off for a bit of hunting first. There are some pyre foxes about halfway between here and the Locus Oasis that he was eyeing up. I bet that's where you'll find him.
* '''Player:''' In that case, I'd better get out there then.
* {{tact|end}}

====Talking to Wolf again====
* '''Guild Hunter Wolf (Master):''' Have you found Fox?
* '''Player:''' I haven't yet. You said he might be hunting pyre foxes, right?
* '''Guild Hunter Wolf (Master):''' That's right. They're about halfway between here and the Locus Oasis.
* '''Player:''' Thanks. I'll head over there.
* {{tact|end}}

===Talking to Verity after speaking to Wolf===
* '''Player:''' It seems like Fox is trying to find something to repair Kiko's bed with.
* '''Guild Scribe Verity:''' Why does that not surprise me? There's two things that man loves: that cat, and not filing in his reports correctly.
* {{tact|end}}

===Talking to Guildmaster Apatura after checking the cat bed===
* '''Guildmaster Apatura:''' Nilsal, hunter.
* '''Player:''' Nilsal, Apatura.
* {{tselect|Select an Option}}
* {{topt|quest=No|What do you do here?}}
* {{topt|Are you free to talk about my quest?}}
** '''Player:''' Are you free to talk about my quest?
** '''Guildmaster Apatura:''' Absolutely.
** '''Player:''' I checked in with Verity and apparently Fox has gone missing.
** '''Guildmaster Apatura:''' Ha, that certainly sounds like Fox! What errand has Wolf got him running this time?
** '''Player:''' How did you know Wolf was involved?
** '''Guildmaster Apatura:''' Let's just say you don't run things around here without good instincts. Let me guess - it's also got something to do with Kiko.
** '''Player:''' That's spot on! How did you know?
** '''Guildmaster Apatura:''' It's an open secret how much Fox and Wolf care about that cat. We all do of course, but those two don't half spoil him rotten.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|quest=No|I'd better be off.}}

==Fox Tracking==
===Talking to Guild Hunter Fox===
* '''Player:''' Are you Fox? Everyone's worried about you.
* '''Guild Hunter Fox:''' Something attacked me in the dark... I can't move much...
* '''Player:''' Can I help you? Maybe patch you up?
* '''Guild Hunter Fox:''' That would be much appreciated! There should be a couple of plants around to make a poultice... Hold it together with an embertailed jerboa tail, and...
* '''Guild Hunter Fox:''' There should be a couple of plants around to make a... make a...
* '''Player:''' Stay with me, Fox! Where are these plants?
* '''Guild Hunter Fox:''' It's a bit fuzzy... I've lost a lot of blood! One should be around here... the other may be near the oasis... with the capybabas... haha, capybaras...
* '''Player:''' And what am I making with them?
* '''Guild Hunter Fox:''' A poultice! And hold it together with the tail from an embertailed jerboa.
* '''Player:''' Plants. Tail. Poultice. On it.
* '''Guild Hunter Fox:''' Don't forget... your traps for the jerboa... they're boxy...
* {{tact|end}}

====Talking to Fox again====
* '''Guild Hunter Fox:''' How's that poul... pool... poultice... Did you find the plants?
* {{tselect|Select an Option}}
* {{topt|I think I've got them both.}}
** '''Player:''' I think I've got them both.
** '''Guild Hunter Fox:''' It doesn't look like you do... Who's the one with the head wound again?
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|Where can I find them?}}
** '''Player:''' Where can I find them?
** '''Guild Hunter Fox:''' It's a bit fuzzy... I've lost a lot of blood! One should be around here... the other may be near the oasis... with the capybabas... haha, capybaras...
** {{tact|end}}

===Talking to Guildmaster Apatura after finding Guild Hunter Fox===
* '''Guildmaster Apatura:''' Nilsal, hunter.
* '''Player:''' Nilsal, Apatura.
* {{tselect|Select an Option}}
* {{topt|quest=No|What do you do here?}}
* {{topt|Are you free to talk about my quest?}}
** '''Player:''' Are you free to talk about my quest?
** '''Guildmaster Apatura:''' Absolutely.
** '''Player:''' Fox has been injured out in the savannah!
** '''Guildmaster Apatura:''' Well, that is impressive. How has he managed that?
** '''Player:''' He said he was attacked by an unknown assailant.
** '''Guildmaster Apatura:'''  Well as you're not offering your condolences, I can only assume he's survived the encounter?
** '''Player:''' He should be fine once I help him make a poultice for the wound.
** '''Guildmaster Apatura:''' Excellent. A final question - was his hand injured?
** '''Player:''' No?
** '''Guildmaster Apatura:''' Wonderful! Then I look foward to reading his report.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|quest=No|I'd better be off.}}

===Talking to Guild Hunter Wolf after talking to Fox===
* '''Player:''' I've found Fox. He's been injured by something out in the savannah.
* '''Guild Hunter Wolf (Master):''' Oh no... I should've offered to go with him. It's never sensible to be out after dark alone...
* '''Player:''' I'm going to do what I can to make sure he's okay.
* '''Guild Hunter Wolf (Master):''' Well thanks for checking in at least. He's still breathing and that's all Fox needs to come out on top.
* {{tact|end}}

===Talking to Guild Scribe Verity after talking to Fox===
* '''Guild Scribe Verity:''' Any updates on Fox?
* '''Player:''' He's been injured out in the savannah, but I'll do my best to make sure he makes it back.
* '''Guild Scribe Verity:''' Tetamo! Only he could get injured on an errand for a cat!
* {{tact|end}}

